ic levels on the brightening economic outlook as more progress was reported on vaccines. Vanguard News Nigeria Energy giant Royal Dutch Shell on Tuesday said it could exit up to 10 countries under a previously announced plan to sell oil and gas assets over two years. June 7, 2016 In "News" Energy giant Saudi Aramco said on Sunday its second-quarter profits plunged a massive 73 percent due to sharply lower oil prices as the coronavirus crisis undercuts global demand. The behemoth, recently dethroned by Apple as the world's most valuable listed company, posted a net profit of $6.6 billion for the… August 9, 2020 In "Energy" Energy giant Saudi Aramco on Tuesday posted a 44.6 per cent slump in third-quarter profit, as the coronavirus pandemic weighs heavily on demand for crude oil. "Net income for the third quarter of 2020 was 44.21 billion Saudi riyals ($11.79 billion)," the company said in a statement, compared to $21.3… November 3, 2020 In "Energy"